# Endpoints & EndpointSlices

Service holds the **selector**; the **resolved Pod IPs** live in a separate object.

- **`Endpoints`** — original, one per Service, same name.
- **`EndpointSlice`** — modern (≥1.21), ≤100 per slice, scales better.

> Filled by the **endpoints controller** as Pods go Ready / not-Ready. `kubectl get endpoints api` = the live answer.

## The #1 Services bug

> `endpoints: <none>` → **no ready Pod matches the selector** — a label typo, unready Pods, or wrong namespace. `kubectl describe service` shows selector + addresses.

## No-selector Service

> Hand-write `Endpoints` → a **Kubernetes name for an external IP** (RDS, legacy VM); swap in-cluster later, clients unchanged.
